<paragraph id="8B8236F1EF3A4A58ABA38BC7FAD1FEA5" blockId="90.[189,1399,1956,2018]" lastBlockId="91.[189,1399,265,362]" lastPageId="91" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3A4A59ABA38BC7FE38F871" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,443,1956,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3A4A59ABA38BC7FE38F871" box="[189,443,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">Glyptapanteles niveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3A4A59AAA18BC6FD96F870" box="[447,533,1957,1983]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3A4A59A9708BC6FD5BF871" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[622,728,1957,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveus">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3A4A59A9708BC6FD5BF871" box="[622,728,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">G.niveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3A4A59AFCF8BC6FAF0F871" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1233,1395,1956,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradfordae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3A4A59AFCF8BC6FAF0F871" box="[1233,1395,1956,1983]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">G.bradfordae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3A4A59ABA38BABFE9BF82D" box="[189,280,1992,2018]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the presence of white distal flagellomeres (at least flagellomeres 10–11), a dark labrum and sparse punctures on the hind coxa (
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3B4A58A9448D6AFC83FEEC" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[602,768,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradfordae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58A9448D6AFC83FEEC" box="[602,768,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">G. bradfordae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3B4A58A8168D6AFCE1FEEC" box="[776,866,265,291]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the flagellomeres 10–11 dark, the labrum pale in colour and denser punctures on the hind coxa). 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3B4A58A8598D4FFBCAFE89" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[839,1097,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58A8598D4FFBCAFE89" box="[839,1097,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Glyptapanteles niveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3B4A58AF4F8D4EFB2FFE88" box="[1105,1196,301,327]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3B4A58ABE38D33FEFAFEA6" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[253,377,336,362]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cooperi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58ABE38D33FEFAFEA6" box="[253,377,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">G. cooperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3B4A58AA9E8D33FE5AFEA5" box="[384,473,336,362]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having a dark labrum (
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3B4A58A8128D33FC0AFEA6" authority="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin, 2022" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[780,905,336,362]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cooperi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58A8128D33FC0AFEA6" box="[780,905,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">G. cooperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A5798EF3B4A58A8918D33FC6AFEA5" box="[911,1001,336,362]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the labrum pale in colour).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C327657AEF3B4A58ABA38DEAFBF4FE3A" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8236F1EF3B4A58ABA38DEAFEC7FE6C" blockId="91.[189,324,393,419]" box="[189,324,393,419]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="D0CA819DEF3B4A58ABA38DEAFEC7FE6C" bold="true" box="[189,324,393,419]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58ABA38DEAFEC7FE6C" bold="true" box="[189,324,393,419]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236F1EF3B4A58ABA38DDBFBF4FE3A" blockId="91.[189,1398,440,502]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
The species epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D72EF3B4A58AAAF8DDAFE7FFE1D" authorityName="Fagan-Jeffries &amp; Bird &amp; Giannotta &amp; Bradford &amp; Austin" authorityYear="2022" box="[433,508,441,466]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Glyptapanteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveus">
<emphasis id="B949EAE3EF3B4A58AAAF8DDAFE7FFE1D" box="[433,508,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">niveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is a Latin adjective meaning ‘snowy’ and refers to the white flagellomeres and white fore coxa, mid coxa, hind- trochanter and anterior metasomal sternites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
